cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Rondo, please cite it as below."
title: "Rondo: scripted multi-provider AI dispatch with a cross-vendor jury"
abstract: >-
  Rondo drives a coding AI in a scripted loop, verifies the work itself (runs the
  tests and hashes the files rather than trusting the model's self-report), and
  convenes a cross-vendor jury — a different vendor independently reviews the
  result, surfacing disagreements as the signal. Multi-provider LLM dispatch
  (Claude, Gemini, Grok, Mistral, OpenAI, Ollama) from MCP, CLI, or Python API.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Hubers
    given-names: Mark
version: 0.7.0
license: MIT
keywords:
  - llm
  - ai-code-review
  - cross-vendor
  - multi-provider
  - dispatch
  - verified-execution
  - mcp
  - agents
